{"article_id":"WBdtsxQdkwZshdlO","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Donald Trump has yielded to political pressure","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"to end the longest US government shutdown in history .","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"After 35 days , he backed a deal","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"to fund federal agencies for three weeks ,","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"but it includes none of the money","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"he has demanded for a US-Mexico border wall .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"The Republican president previously vowed to reject any budget","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"unless it included $ 5.7bn","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"( £4.3bn )","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"to fund his signature campaign pledge .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"But Democrats ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"who control the House of Representatives ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"flatly refused .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"Later on Friday , the Senate and House unanimously passed a bill","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"to temporarily end the shutdown ,","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"after which President Trump signed the bill into law .","depth":5},{"id":16,"text":"Following the votes in Congress ,","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"Mr Trump tweeted","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"that his decision had been `` in no way a concession '' ,","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"but was `` taking care of the millions of people","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"who were getting badly hurt by the shutdown '' .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Speaking in the White House Rose Garden ,","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"Mr Trump said","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"he was `` very proud to announce '' the agreement ,","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"which will fund the government until 15 February .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"He said","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"federal workers","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"affected by the political imbroglio ,","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"whom he called `` incredible patriots '' ,","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"would receive full back-pay .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"Mr Trump also said","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"he would not yet resort to `` a very powerful alternative ''","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"- an apparent reference to declaring a national emergency .","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"This could divert military funding towards building a southern border wall ,","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"but such a proclamation would provoke constitutional uproar and legal challenges .","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"However , the president added :","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"`` We really have no choice","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"but to build a powerful wall or steel barrier . ``","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"If we do n't get a fair deal from Congress","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"the government will either shut down on February 15 again ,","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"or I will use the powers","depth":15},{"id":41,"text":"afforded to me under the laws and the constitution of the United States","depth":15},{"id":42,"text":"to address this emergency . ''","depth":14},{"id":43,"text":"Mr Trump accepted the deal","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"after hearing of the shutdown 's strain on law enforcement agencies ,","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"an administration official told Reuters news agency .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"The president is prepared to haggle on the $ 5.7bn","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"he has been demanding for the border barrier ,","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"the same official said .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"For more than a month , Donald Trump insisted","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"he would not support reopening the federal government","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"without funding for his border wall .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"On Friday ,","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"as the fallout from the partial shutdown sent tremors through the US aviation system ,","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"the president backed down .","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"Before all this began ,","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"Republican Senate majority leader Mitch McConnell reportedly warned the president","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"that there was no clear way","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"to win a shutdown standoff with Democrats ,","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"who","depth":16},{"id":60,"text":"- flush off their November election victories -","depth":16},{"id":61,"text":"would n't relent .","depth":15},{"id":62,"text":"The wily Kentucky senator , with more than a few legislative victories under his belt , was vindicated .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"That must be cold comfort for congressional Republicans ,","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"who have watched their party","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"- and the president -","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"take the brunt of the blame for the impasse .","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"And it now sets up a three-week period of frenetic negotiations","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"to reach a border security agreement .","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"If the federal employees have been drowning","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"because of the shutdown ,","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"this temporary funding agreement gives them a chance for a desperate gulp of air .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"In three weeks , another shutdown looms , however .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"Or ,","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"the president warned ,","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"he could declare a national emergency","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"and take the border battle to the courts .","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"Either way , the president has retreated","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"- but the fight is far from over .","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"With opinion polls showing","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"most Americans blamed Mr Trump for the shutdown ,","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"he opted for a way out","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"that had been pushed for weeks by the Democratic leader of the House , Speaker Nancy Pelosi .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"The outcome was widely seen as a resounding victory for her .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"Lawmakers in her party lavished praise on the California congresswoman 's refusal","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"to give ground .","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"`` Trump is a broken man .","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"It 's over for him , ''","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"tweeted commentator Mike Cernovich ,","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"who has a large social media following of the president 's voters .","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"He said","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"Mr Trump had been outmanoeuvred by the `` alpha '' House speaker .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"Headlines on the conservative Drudge Report and Breitbart News screamed in red letters","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"that there would be no wall funds .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Right-wing commentator Ann Coulter called Mr Trump `` the biggest wimp ever","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"to serve as president '' .","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"Robert Reich ,","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"who served as labour secretary under Presidents Gerald Ford , Jimmy Carter and Bill Clinton ,","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"tweeted","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"that Mr Trump had thrown a tantrum","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"and got `` nothing '' .","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"Some 800,000 civil servants missed another payday on Friday amid the five-week closure of about a quarter of the federal government .","depth":4},{"id":102,"text":"Earlier on Friday , hundreds of flights were grounded or delayed at US airports","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"because of unpaid air traffic controllers","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"calling in sick .","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"The Federal Aviation Administration","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"( FAA )","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"halted arrivals for about an hour at New York 's LaGuardia Airport .","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"Flights were also delayed at Newark Liberty International Airport and Philadelphia International Airport","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"because of staff shortages ,","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"the FAA said .","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"Meanwhile , thousands of Internal Revenue Service","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"( IRS )","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"employees failed to show up","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"after they were ordered to return to work unpaid ,","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"the Washington Post reported .","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"The Trump administration recalled 26,000 IRS workers this week","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"to handle the looming tax filing season .","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"But about 14,000 of them did not come back as of Tuesday ,","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"IRS officials told members of Congress .","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"FBI Director Christopher Wray said in a video message to agents on Friday :","depth":6},{"id":121,"text":"`` I 'm about as angry","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"as I 've been in a long , long time . ''","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"He said of the shutdown 's effects on his agency :","depth":6},{"id":124,"text":"`` It 's mind-boggling ,","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"it 's short-sighted ,","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"and it 's unfair . ''","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"His remarks came","depth":5},{"id":128,"text":"after an FBI report this week revealed","depth":6},{"id":129,"text":"its resources were at `` breaking point '' .","depth":6},{"id":130,"text":"Please include a contact number","depth":3},{"id":131,"text":"if you are willing to speak to a BBC journalist .","depth":3},{"id":132,"text":"You can also contact us in the following ways :","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":265,"left":262,"right":264,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":262,"left":233,"right":261,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":233,"left":148,"right":232,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":145,"right":147,"relation":"elabor